920.question: When they say "comparable performance", how much of a performance drop do these new embeddings result in?
920.response: {'Answer': 'The proposed embeddings result in a performance drop of 2.2 in MRR and 10 points in MR for link prediction, while there is a 1.6 performance gain in Hits@10%. For triple classification, the proposed method shows an improvement of 0.3% in AUC and 4.4% in accuracy. Finally, for interpretability, there is an improvement in AutoWI@5% from 6 to 66, in Coherence@5 from -47.4 to -12.5, and in Manual WI(%) from 12% to 84%.'}
920.answer: Performance was comparable, with the proposed method quite close and sometimes exceeding performance of baseline method.
